Vector Search Query Pre-Filtering

Enhance your vector search queries with pre-filtering fields. Use logical operators and manage case sensitivity for field names and values to ensure precise data retrieval.

Supported Operators

Use these logical operators to test the values in each pre-filtering field.

DATA TYPE	SUPPORTED OPERATORS
Number and Percent	
<  (Less than)
<= (Less than or equal to)
=  (Equal to)
> (Greater than)
>= (Greater than or equal to)

Date and DateTime	

=  (Equal to)

Examples:

DateTimeField='’2024-05-21 00:00:00.000000 UTC'’
DateField=''2024-05-21''

Timezone can be any standard timezone, such as UTC, PST, or EST, or it can be an offset, such as +05:30 or -08:00. If you specify no timezone, the system assumes UTC.


Text, URL, Email, and Phone	
=  (Equal to)
!= (Not Equal to)
in (‘option1’, ‘option2’, ‘option3’) -> To match any of the listed options. A maximum of 10 options can be provided.
not in (‘option1’, ‘option2’, ‘option3’) -> To match none of the listed options. A maximum of 10 options can be provided.

Boolean	

= (Equal to)

Example: <BooleanField>=true

Combining Filters

You can combine individual filters using the logical and and or operators.

For example:

'TextField1 != "value1"' and
BooleanField2 = true and
('TextField2 = "value2"' or
TextField3 not in ("a", "b", "c") or
TextField4 in ('a', 'b', 'c')
) and
NumberField1=3.1415 and
DateTimeField='2024-06-04 00:00:00.000000 UTC'

Case Sensitivity on Pre-filtering Fields

Names of pre-filtering fields are case insensitive. For example, if the name of a field is My_Column_c , a filter expression with my_column_c correctly references that field. However, case matters for values used within filters. If the field has a value SomeValue,  the filter expression My_Column_c='somevalue' or My_Column_c='SOMEVALUE' results in a no-match—only the expression My_Column_c='SomeValue' matches that record.

Default Pre-filtering Fields

The field DataSource__c from the chunk data model object (CDMO) is a default pre-filtering field. It is always available in pre-filtering queries.
